{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The average result of 200 users is the final indicator for performance comparison.",
    "For each user from the sample set, we sort all items that the user interacts with in the chronological order.",
    "Then, we evaluate the results based on the leave-one-out strategy and treat the last interacted item as the ground truth.",
    "For performance comparison, we fix the length of candidate items to 20 as in [44], and mix the other 19 items from the ground truth in random positions by default.",
    "As for evaluation, we utilize two widely used ranking metrics in recommender systems, i.e., Recall [6] and Normalized Discounted Cumulated Gain (NDCG) [48]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
